Del Valle Rd. at Mendenhall Rd.
Murieta pond (Hwy 16 west of Rancho Murieta)

Observation Details: This specimen spotted me earlier in the hunt and submarined, that is, submerged without the usual bill-first dive. It simply sank straight down, it's neck and head still in swimming position, disappearing like a preiscope. No splash, no noise.
He was just minding his own business but must have been using the favorite perch of a pair of TRSW. They hectored the EABL until it moved to the next post.
